[2] UK (Shropshire, England)
Date: Mon 6 May 2013
Source: The Shropshire Star [edited]
http://www.shropshirestar.com/news/health/2013/05/06/measles-cases-in-shropshire-rise-to-41/


There are now 41 reported cases of measles in Shropshire -- with more than half in the Oswestry area, new figures showed today [6 May 2013].

Meanwhile, health bosses across the border in Mid Wales say up to 3000 youngsters aged between 10 and 18 in the region have still not been vaccinated against the disease. Bosses at Public Health England West Midlands say from January to 2 May [2013] there have been 35 suspected cases of measles in Shropshire and 6 diagnosed cases in the county. They say therefore the total number of reported cases for Shropshire as of [2 May 2013] was 41. 5 out of 6 six confirmed cases were reported in Oswestry. 18 out of the 35 suspected cases were also reported in Oswestry.

