[4] UK (Ayrshire, Scotland)
Date: Fri 10 May 2013
Source: Irvine Times [edited]
http://www.irvinetimes.com/news/irvine/articles/2013/05/10/456950-measles-outbreak-in-ayrshire/


The Public Health department says they have investigated 5 confirmed cases of measles in Ayrshire [southwest Scotland] within the last 3 weeks. All 5 cases are thought to be linked and appropriate public health measures have been taken. The news will surely concern parents but health bosses at NHS Ayrshire and Arran are refusing to confirm where in Ayrshire the outbreak has occurred. They have confirmed, however that the families and close contacts of the cases and offered advice and MMR vaccination or immunoglobulin as required.

NHS bosses say there is no known connection to the measles outbreak in Ayrshire to those cases in Wales and England.

[Byline: Lisa Hodge]

